Error running script: Error adding key 'touch' to dictionary: An item with the same key has already been added. Key: touch
 Welcome to The Zen Garden (Quest v5.3).

This is a text-only brainteaser (with some sound) inspired by Japanese art and haiku.

It's not easy!

It has been designed to be explored and contemplated over endless cups of green tea.

 A few hints before you start:.

Examine everything in the game thoroughly. There are a few red herrings, but most things are significant.

Read location descriptions carefully - things do not always stay the same!

In general, expect to find subtle clues rather than explicit solutions.

If you expect something to work and it doesn't, try using full words.

Interrogate the characters you encounter. Don't forget to ASK (person) ABOUT (thing), and that (thing) must be a full word. Some characters are more talkative than others. All have at least something to tell you.

Good luck and please let me know how you get on!

You are in a Zen Garden.

There is a small lake with a wooden bridge.

In the centre of the lake is a flat rock.

A heron stands quite motionless in the shallows.

There is a teahouse in the eastern corner of the garden.

You can also see a young woman standing on the bridge, an old man sitting on the floor of the teahouse and a sparrow singing in a willow tree.

You can go east into the teahouse or out of the garden.
